OL,3,CEngland's river health classifications
OL,4,Crelying on old data, campaigners warn
OL,6,FOfficial classifications of the health
OL,7,Fof England's rivers could be relying
OL,8,Fon data that is up to a decade old,
OL,9,Fcampaigners have warned.
OL,11,FTo assess the ecological status of a
OL,12,Friver, the watchdog uses several
OL,13,Fmetrics, including the analysis of
OL,14,Finvertebrates in samples collected
OL,15,Ffrom watercourses, such as mayfly
OL,16,Flarvae, worms, snails, dragonflies or
OL,17,Fshrimps.
