OL,3,CEngland's river health classifications
OL,4,Crelying on old data, campaigners warn
OL,6,FJanina Gray, head of science and
OL,7,Fpolicy at WildFish, said: "The public
OL,8,Fand those who work to protect our
OL,9,Frivers I think will be surprised and
OL,10,Fdismayed to find out the data used by
OL,11,Fregulators to assess our rivers is so
OL,12,Fout of date.
OL,14,F"Protecting our rivers starts with us
OL,15,Fall working together to ensure we have
OL,16,Ftransparent, accurate and current data
OL,17,Fthat can be used not only to identify
OL,18,Fenvironmental stressors but also track
OL,19,Fprogress.
